t/grid#styling","content":"Styling"},"633":{"id":"/docs/layout/grid-27","page_id":"/docs/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/layout/grid#basic-example","content":"The Grid uses the `Container`, `Row`, and `Col` components to create responsive layouts. It is built with flexbox and adapts to different screen sizes."},"634":{"id":"/docs/layout/grid-28","page_id":"/docs/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/layout/grid#auto-layout-columns","content":"Breakpoint props allow easy sizing of columns without setting an explicit numbered span."},"635":{"id":"/docs/layout/grid-29","page_id":"/docs/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/layout/grid#equal-width","content":"A `Col` without any props creates equal-width columns for every screen size."},"636":{"id":"/docs/layout/grid-30","page_id":"/docs/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/layout/grid#variable-width-content","content":"Setting a breakpoint prop to `\"auto\"` sizes the column based on the natural width of its content."},"637":{"id":"/docs/layout/grid-31","page_id":"/docs/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/layout/grid#responsive-props","content":"The `xs`, `sm`, `md`, `lg`, `xl`, and `xxl` props specify different column sizes for different screen sizes. Breakpoints are defined using minimum widths, meaning each one applies from that width upward. For example, `md={4}` applies to medium devices (tablets) and above, and renders the `md:col-4` class."},"638":{"id":"/docs/layout/grid-32","page_id":"/docs/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/layout/grid#all-breakpoints","content":"For grids that are the same across all breakpoints, plain `Col` and the `xs` prop are enough."},"639":{"id":"/docs/layout/grid-33","page_id":"/docs/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/layout/grid#mix-and-match","content":"Different breakpoint props can be combined on the same column for different screen sizes."},"640":{"id":"/docs/layout/grid-34","page_id":"/docs/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/layout/grid#row-columns","content":"Instead of sizing each column, the `Row` breakpoint props set the number of columns per row. The grid automatically lays out the columns evenly, and `\"auto\"` sizes them based on their content."},"641":{"id":"/docs/layout/grid-35","page_id":"/docs/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/layout/grid#nesting","content":"Nesting works by placing a new `Row` and set of `Col` components inside an existing `Col`. This gives more control over the layout of the content."},"642":{"id":"/docs/layout/grid-36","page_id":"/docs/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/layout/grid#columns","content":"Columns can be modified with options for alignment, ordering, and offsetting using the flexbox grid system."},"643":{"id":"/docs/layout/grid-37","page_id":"/docs/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/layout/grid#vertical-alignment","content":"The `items-start`, `items-center`, and `items-end` classes on `Row` control vertical alignment of all columns."},"644":{"id":"/docs/layout/grid-38","page_id":"/docs/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/layout/grid#vertical-alignment","content":"The `self-start`, `self-center`, and `self-end` classes control vertical alignment of individual columns."},"645":{"id":"/docs/layout/grid-39","page_id":"/docs/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/layout/grid#horizontal-alignment","content":"The `justify-*` classes on `Row` control horizontal alignment."},"646":{"id":"/docs/layout/grid-40","page_id":"/docs/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/layout/grid#order-classes","content":"The `order-{number}` classes change the visual order of columns."},"647":{"id":"/docs/layout/grid-41","page_id":"/docs/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/layout/grid#offsetting-columns","content":"The object form of a breakpoint prop moves columns to the right. For example, `md={{ span: 4, offset: 4 }