ally stacked set of interactive headings that each reveal a section of content."],[712,"Accepts the same `variant`, `size`, `color`, `state`, `asChild`, and `className` props as `FormControl`."],[1,"Accordion"],[234,"Actionable"],[439,"Actions colors (generate all color-related utilities)"],[258,"Active"],[356,"Active"],[233,"Active and disabled"],[396,"Add `disabled` to a `TabsTrigger` to prevent its panel from being selected."],[10,"Add `disabled` to an `AccordionItem` to prevent it from opening, or to the\n`Accordion` root to disable every item."],[508,"Address"],[15,"Alert"],[22,"Alert"],[23,"AlertIcon"],[612,"All breakpoints"],[460,"All components accept a `className` prop. Custom classes are merged with the component classes, so any Tailwind utility can be applied on top. For example, rounded pill buttons can be created by adding the `rounded-full` class."],[816,"All components accept a `className` prop. Custom classes are merged with the component classes, so Tailwind utility classes can be used to adjust any component."],[483,"All components rely on the same semantic tokens:"],[592,"All Tailwind utility classes can be applied to Hummingbird React components through the `className` prop. Custom classes are merged with the component classes, so utilities can adjust spacing, typography, radius, and more without writing custom CSS. This page lists the most frequently used utilities; see the official Tailwind CSS docs for the complete reference."],[517,"All the headings (`h1` to `h6`) in Hummingbird are styled with CSS variables for font size, weight, line height, and margin."],[279,"Always collapsed"],[43,"An avatar renders an image with a fallback for when the image is unavailable."],[148,"An icon-only button for dismissing content."],[33,"An image element with a text fallback for representing a user or entity."],[163,"An interactive component that expands and collapses a single panel of content."],[6,"API Reference"],[21,"API Reference"],[39,"API Reference"],[